keys.name: CFG-NMEA-COMPAT
keys.description:
Enable compatibility mode
This might be needed for certain applications, e.g. for an NMEA parser that expects a fixed number of digits in position coordinates.

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-CONSIDER
keys.description:
Enable considering mode
This will affect NMEA output used satellite count. If set, also considered satellites (e.g. RAIMED) are counted as used satellites as well.

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-LIMIT82
keys.description:
Enable strict limit to 82 characters maximum
NMEA message length

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-HIGHPREC
keys.description:
Enable high precision mode
This flag cannot be set in conjunction with either CFG-NMEA-COMPAT or CFG-NMEA-LIMIT82 mode.

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-SVNUMBERING
keys.description:
Display configuration for SVs that do not have
value defined in NMEA

keys.description:
RTCM DF003 (Reference station ID) output
value
Value to set in RTCM data field DF003 (Reference station ID) in RTCM output messages containing DF003. The value
can be 0..4095.

keys.name: CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN
keys.description:
RTCM DF003 (Reference station ID) input value
Value to use for filtering out RTCM input messages based on their DF003 data field (Reference station ID) value. To be
used in conjunction with CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN_FILTER. The value can be 0..4095.

keys.name: CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN_FILTER
keys.description:
RTCM input filter configuration based on RTCM
DF003 (Reference station ID) value
Configures if and how the filtering out of RTCM input messages based on their DF003 data field (Reference station ID)
operates.
See Table 53 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

values.name: DISABLED
values.description: Disabled RTCM input filter; all input messages allowed

values.name: RELAXED
values.description:
Relaxed RTCM input filter; input messages allowed must contain a
DF003 data field matching the CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN value or not
contain by specification the DF003 data field

values.name: STRICT
values.description:
Strict RTCM input filter; input messages allowed must contain a
DF003 data field matching the CFG-RTCM-DF003 value

keys.name: CFG-SBAS-PRNSCANMASK
keys.description:

This configuration item determines which SBAS PRNs should be searched. Setting it to 0 indicates auto-scanning all
SBAS PRNs. For non-zero values the bits correspond to the allocated SBAS PRNs ranging from PRN120 (bit 0) to PRN158
(bit 38), where a bit set enables searching for the corresponding PRN.
See Table 55 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

bits.name: ALL

Must be set for frequency-time products.

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1
keys.description:
Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock
(TP1)
If set, sync to GNSS if GNSS time is valid otherwise, if not set or not available, use local clock.
Ignored by time-frequency product variants, which will attempt to use the best available time/frequency reference (not
necessarily GNSS).
This flag can be unset only in Timing product variants.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1
keys.description:
Use locked parameters when possible (TP1)
If set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1 as soon as GNSS time is valid. Otherwise if not valid
or not set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_TP1.

keys.name: CFG-TP-ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1
keys.description:
Align time pulse to top of second (TP1)
To use this feature, CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 must be set.
Time pulse period must be an integer fraction of 1 second.
Ignored in time-frequency product variants, where it is assumed always enabled. Set maxSlewRate and
maxPhaseCorrRate fields of UBX-CFG-SMGR to 0 to disable alignment.

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP1
keys.description:

true (1): rising edge at top of second.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP1
keys.description:

Only relevant if CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 and ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1 are set.
Note that configured GNSS time is estimated by the receiver if locked to any GNSS system. If the receiver has a valid
GNSS fix it will attempt to steer the TP to the specified time grid even if the specified time is not based on information
from the constellation's satellites. To ensure timing based purely on a given GNSS, restrict the supported constellations
in CFG-SIGNAL-*.
See Table 67 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-MAINTALKERID

By default the main Talker ID (i.e. the Talker ID used for all messages other than GSV) is determined by the GNSS
assignment of the receiver's channels (see CFG-SIGNAL).
This field enables the main Talker ID to be overridden.

values.name: AUTO
values.description: Main Talker ID is not overridden

values.name: GA
values.description: Set main Talker ID to 'GA' (not available in all products)

values.name: GB

values.name: GQ

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-GSVTALKERID
keys.description:

values.name: GNSS
values.description: Use GNSS-specific Talker ID (as defined by NMEA)

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-BDSTALKERID
keys.description:

keys.name: CFG-RTCM-DF003_OUT
keys.description:
RTCM DF003 (Reference station ID) output
value
Value to set in RTCM data field DF003 (Reference station ID) in RTCM output messages containing DF003. The value
can be 0..4095.

keys.name: CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN
keys.description:
RTCM DF003 (Reference station ID) input value
Value to use for filtering out RTCM input messages based on their DF003 data field (Reference station ID) value. To be
used in conjunction with CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN_FILTER. The value can be 0..4095.

keys.name: CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN_FILTER
keys.description:
RTCM input filter configuration based on RTCM
DF003 (Reference station ID) value
Configures if and how the filtering out of RTCM input messages based on their DF003 data field (Reference station ID)
operates.
See Table 53 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

values.name: DISABLED
values.description: Disabled RTCM input filter; all input messages allowed

values.name: RELAXED
values.description:
Relaxed RTCM input filter; input messages allowed must contain a
DF003 data field matching the CFG-RTCM-DF003_IN value or not
contain by specification the DF003 data field

values.name: STRICT
values.description:
Strict RTCM input filter; input messages allowed must contain a
DF003 data field matching the CFG-RTCM-DF003 value

msg 0)

keys.name: CFG-SBAS-PRNSCANMASK
keys.description:

This configuration item determines which SBAS PRNs should be searched. Setting it to 0 indicates auto-scanning all
SBAS PRNs. For non-zero values the bits correspond to the allocated SBAS PRNs ranging from PRN120 (bit 0) to PRN158
(bit 38), where a bit set enables searching for the corresponding PRN.
See Table 55 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

bits.name: ALL
bits.description: Enable search for all SBAS PRNS

keys.name: CFG-SEC-CFG_LOCK_UNLOCKGRP2
keys.description:

the configuration lockdown has been enabled.

Enable the first timepulse

Must be set for frequency-time products.

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1
keys.description:
Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock
(TP1)
If set, sync to GNSS if GNSS time is valid otherwise, if not set or not available, use local clock.
Ignored by time-frequency product variants, which will attempt to use the best available time/frequency reference (not
necessarily GNSS).
This flag can be unset only in Timing product variants.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1
keys.description:
Use locked parameters when possible (TP1)
If set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1 as soon as GNSS time is valid. Otherwise if not valid
or not set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_TP1.

keys.name: CFG-TP-ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1
keys.description:
Align time pulse to top of second (TP1)
To use this feature, CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 must be set.
Time pulse period must be an integer fraction of 1 second.
Ignored in time-frequency product variants, where it is assumed always enabled. Set maxSlewRate and
maxPhaseCorrRate fields of UBX-CFG-SMGR to 0 to disable alignment.

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP1
keys.description:

true (1): rising edge at top of second.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP1
keys.description:

Only relevant if CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 and ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1 are set.
Note that configured GNSS time is estimated by the receiver if locked to any GNSS system. If the receiver has a valid
GNSS fix it will attempt to steer the TP to the specified time grid even if the specified time is not based on information
from the constellation's satellites. To ensure timing based purely on a given GNSS, restrict the supported constellations
in CFG-SIGNAL-*.
See Table 67 below for a list of possible constants for this item.
